The spectra of a network can be divided into two parts, (i) bulk part consisting of non-degenerative eigenvalues, (ii) extremal and degenerative eigenvalue. The basic investigation of bulk part of eigenvalues is carried out through their density distribution. The spectral density of a graph is the density of the eigenvalues of its adjacency matrix. For a finite system, this can be written as a sum of δ functions as, 
